abstract: Bernie Sanders' Democratic presidential rivals warn that nominating the self-described democratic socialist will ensure President Donald Trump's re-election, but a growing number of the party's voters see the senator as their best chance of winning in November.

lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — Bernie Sanders' Democratic presidential rivals warn that nominating the self-described democratic socialist will ensure President Donald Trump's re-election, but a growing number of the party's voters see the senator as their best chance of winning in November.
headline_main: Can Sanders Beat Trump? A Growing Number of Democratic Voters Say Yes
headline_print_headline: Can Sanders Beat Trump? A Growing Number of Democratic Voters Say Yes

abstract: Democratic presidential contender Joe Biden won the endorsement of an influential black congressman from South Carolina on Wednesday, three days before the state's primary where he is competing with national front-runner Bernie Sanders for the crucial African-American vote.
snippet: Democratic presidential contender Joe Biden won the endorsement of an influential black congressman from South Carolina on Wednesday, three days before the state's primary where he is competing with national front-runner Bernie Sanders for the cru...
lead_paragraph: CHARLESTON, S.C. — Democratic presidential contender Joe Biden won the endorsement of an influential black congressman from South Carolina on Wednesday, three days before the state's primary where he is competing with national front-runner Bernie Sanders for the crucial African-American vote.
headline_main: Biden Lands Key Endorsement Three Days Before South Carolina Presidential Contest
headline_print_headline: Biden Lands Key Endorsement Three Days Before South Carolina Presidential Contest

headline_main: Winners and Losers of the Democratic Debate
byline_original: By The New York Times Opinion

abstract: Trevor Noah provided commentary on Tuesday night’s Democratic debate in South Carolina, or, as “The Daily Show” called it, “Finally, a state with black voters.”

abstract: Eyeing a South Carolina victory to rescue his presidential ambitions, Joe Biden claimed one of the state's most coveted endorsements on Wednesday as Democratic front-runner Bernie Sanders marched past the blistering assault from his rivals on the debate stage the night before.

lead_paragraph: CHARLESTON, S.C. — Eyeing a South Carolina victory to rescue his presidential ambitions, Joe Biden claimed one of the state's most coveted endorsements on Wednesday as Democratic front-runner Bernie Sanders marched past the blistering assault from his rivals on the debate stage the night before.
